  26 class BasicTests(fixtures.DistInfoPkg, unittest.TestCase):
  27     version_pattern = r'\d+\.\d+(\.\d)?'
  28 
  29     def test_retrieves_version_of_self(self):
  30         dist = Distribution.from_name('distinfo-pkg')
  31         assert isinstance(dist.version, text)
  32         assert re.match(self.version_pattern, dist.version)
  33 
  34     def test_for_name_does_not_exist(self):
  35         with self.assertRaises(PackageNotFoundError):
  36             Distribution.from_name('does-not-exist')
  37 
  38     def test_new_style_classes(self):
  39         self.assertIsInstance(Distribution, type)
  40         self.assertIsInstance(MetadataPathFinder, type)

  43 class ImportTests(fixtures.DistInfoPkg, unittest.TestCase):
  44     def test_import_nonexistent_module(self):
  45         # Ensure that the MetadataPathFinder does not crash an import of a
  46         # non-existent module.
  47         with self.assertRaises(ImportError):
  48             importlib.import_module('does_not_exist')
  49 
  50     def test_resolve(self):
  51         entries = dict(entry_points()['entries'])
  52         ep = entries['main']
  53         self.assertEqual(ep.load().__name__, "main")
  54 
  55     def test_entrypoint_with_colon_in_name(self):
  56         entries = dict(entry_points()['entries'])
  57         ep = entries['ns:sub']
  58         self.assertEqual(ep.value, 'mod:main')
  59 
  60     def test_resolve_without_attr(self):
  61         ep = EntryPoint(
  62             name='ep',
  63             value='importlib_metadata',
  64             group='grp',
  65             )
  66         assert ep.load() is importlib_metadata

  69 class NameNormalizationTests(
  70         fixtures.OnSysPath, fixtures.SiteDir, unittest.TestCase):
  71     @staticmethod
  72     def pkg_with_dashes(site_dir):
  73         """
  74         Create minimal metadata for a package with dashes
  75         in the name (and thus underscores in the filename).
  76         """
  77         metadata_dir = site_dir / 'my_pkg.dist-info'
  78         metadata_dir.mkdir()
  79         metadata = metadata_dir / 'METADATA'
  80         with metadata.open('w') as strm:
  81             strm.write('Version: 1.0\n')
  82         return 'my-pkg'
  83 
  84     def test_dashes_in_dist_name_found_as_underscores(self):
  85         """
  86         For a package with a dash in the name, the dist-info metadata
  87         uses underscores in the name. Ensure the metadata loads.
  88         """
  89         pkg_name = self.pkg_with_dashes(self.site_dir)
  90         assert version(pkg_name) == '1.0'
  91 
  92     @staticmethod
  93     def pkg_with_mixed_case(site_dir):
  94         """
  95         Create minimal metadata for a package with mixed case
  96         in the name.
  97         """
  98         metadata_dir = site_dir / 'CherryPy.dist-info'
  99         metadata_dir.mkdir()
 100         metadata = metadata_dir / 'METADATA'
 101         with metadata.open('w') as strm:
 102             strm.write('Version: 1.0\n')
 103         return 'CherryPy'
 104 
 105     def test_dist_name_found_as_any_case(self):
 106         """
 107         Ensure the metadata loads when queried with any case.
 108         """
 109         pkg_name = self.pkg_with_mixed_case(self.site_dir)
 110         assert version(pkg_name) == '1.0'
 111         assert version(pkg_name.lower()) == '1.0'
 112         assert version(pkg_name.upper()) == '1.0'

 115 class NonASCIITests(fixtures.OnSysPath, fixtures.SiteDir, unittest.TestCase):
 116     @staticmethod
 117     def pkg_with_non_ascii_description(site_dir):
 118         """
 119         Create minimal metadata for a package with non-ASCII in
 120         the description.
 121         """
 122         metadata_dir = site_dir / 'portend.dist-info'
 123         metadata_dir.mkdir()
 124         metadata = metadata_dir / 'METADATA'
 125         with metadata.open('w', encoding='utf-8') as fp:
 126             fp.write('Description: pôrˈtend\n')
 127         return 'portend'
 128 
 129     @staticmethod
 130     def pkg_with_non_ascii_description_egg_info(site_dir):
 131         """
 132         Create minimal metadata for an egg-info package with
 133         non-ASCII in the description.
 134         """
 135         metadata_dir = site_dir / 'portend.dist-info'
 136         metadata_dir.mkdir()
 137         metadata = metadata_dir / 'METADATA'
 138         with metadata.open('w', encoding='utf-8') as fp:
 139             fp.write(textwrap.dedent("""
 140                 Name: portend
 141 
 142                 pôrˈtend
 143                 """).lstrip())
 144         return 'portend'
 145 
 146     def test_metadata_loads(self):
 147         pkg_name = self.pkg_with_non_ascii_description(self.site_dir)
 148         meta = metadata(pkg_name)
 149         assert meta['Description'] == 'pôrˈtend'
 150 
 151     def test_metadata_loads_egg_info(self):
 152         pkg_name = self.pkg_with_non_ascii_description_egg_info(self.site_dir)
 153         meta = metadata(pkg_name)
 154         assert meta.get_payload() == 'pôrˈtend\n'

 157 class DiscoveryTests(fixtures.EggInfoPkg,
 158                      fixtures.DistInfoPkg,
 159                      unittest.TestCase):
 160 
 161     def test_package_discovery(self):
 162         dists = list(distributions())
 163         assert all(
 164             isinstance(dist, Distribution)
 165             for dist in dists
 166             )
 167         assert any(
 168             dist.metadata['Name'] == 'egginfo-pkg'
 169             for dist in dists
 170             )
 171         assert any(
 172             dist.metadata['Name'] == 'distinfo-pkg'
 173             for dist in dists
 174             )
 175 
 176     def test_invalid_usage(self):
 177         with self.assertRaises(ValueError):
 178             list(distributions(context='something', name='else'))

 181 class DirectoryTest(fixtures.OnSysPath, fixtures.SiteDir, unittest.TestCase):
 182     def test_egg_info(self):
 183         # make an `EGG-INFO` directory that's unrelated
 184         self.site_dir.joinpath('EGG-INFO').mkdir()
 185         # used to crash with `IsADirectoryError`
 186         with self.assertRaises(PackageNotFoundError):
 187             version('unknown-package')
 188 
 189     def test_egg(self):
 190         egg = self.site_dir.joinpath('foo-3.6.egg')
 191         egg.mkdir()
 192         with self.add_sys_path(egg):
 193             with self.assertRaises(PackageNotFoundError):
 194                 version('foo')

 224 class TestEntryPoints(unittest.TestCase):
 225     def __init__(self, *args):
 226         super(TestEntryPoints, self).__init__(*args)
 227         self.ep = importlib_metadata.EntryPoint('name', 'value', 'group')
 228 
 229     def test_entry_point_pickleable(self):
 230         revived = pickle.loads(pickle.dumps(self.ep))
 231         assert revived == self.ep
 232 
 233     def test_immutable(self):
 234         """EntryPoints should be immutable"""
 235         with self.assertRaises(AttributeError):
 236             self.ep.name = 'badactor'
 237 
 238     def test_repr(self):
 239         assert 'EntryPoint' in repr(self.ep)
 240         assert 'name=' in repr(self.ep)
 241         assert "'name'" in repr(self.ep)
 242 
 243     def test_hashable(self):
 244         """EntryPoints should be hashable"""
 245         hash(self.ep)
 246 
 247     def test_json_dump(self):
 248         """
 249         json should not expect to be able to dump an EntryPoint
 250         """
 251         with self.assertRaises(Exception):
 252             json.dumps(self.ep)
 253 
 254     def test_module(self):
 255         assert self.ep.module == 'value'
 256 
 257     def test_attr(self):
 258         assert self.ep.attr is None
